git init --> initialise local repository

git remote add origin "URL" --> adds remote repository and its URL

git pull origin master --> pulls remote repository from github .

git status --> tell which files are added and are ready to commit.

git add --> lets you add files to your index

git commit --> it refers to a recording snapshot of repository at given time.

git add . --> Adds every file to your index.

git commit -a -m "" -->commit all the files 

git log --> gives log

git branch branch_name -->creartes new branch. 

git checkout branch_name --> switch branch to branch_name.

git merge branch_name --> (be in destination branch ie master) then merge the branch.

git pull=git fetch + git merge

git push origin master --> pushes everything to central repository.

git checkout hex-code filename -->revert back to the changes.

gitignore - Specifies intentionally untracked files to ignore
echo 'pattern/' >> .gitignore
